# API Architecture Guidelines

## Response Interfaces
Define clear interface hierarchies for API responses:

```typescript
interface BaseResponse<T> {
  endpoint: string;
  path: string;
  dateRange: {
    startDate: string;
    endDate: string;
  };
  result: T;
  timeBreakdown?: {
    daily: Array<{ date: string; metrics: T }>;
    monthly: Array<{ month: string; metrics: T }>;
  };
}
```

## Parameter Validation
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all API parameters
- Include optional parameters with clear defaults
- Document parameter constraints in interface definitions

Example:
```typescript
interface AnalyticsParams {
  url: string;
  startDate?: string;
  endDate?: string;
  timeframe?: string;
  limit?: number;
}
```

## Error Handling
- Use structured error responses
- Include appropriate HTTP status codes
- Provide detailed error messages in development
- Sanitize error details in production

## Logging
Use the debug utility for consistent logging:
```typescript
debugLog("info", "Operation description", {
  contextData: value,
  additionalInfo: details
});
```

## API Documentation
- Document all endpoints with JSDoc comments
- Include parameter descriptions and constraints
- Provide example requests and responses
- Note any rate limits or usage restrictions

## Request Processing
- Validate input parameters before processing
- Use utility functions for common operations
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Cache expensive operations where appropriate
